changelogs.title: Cockpit feature request is completed
changelogs.description: CHANGED: We are happy to announce that we closed one of the most wanted features at Scaleway (open since Jan. 21). Almost every Scaleway products are available in Cockpit for metrics and/or logs. New features and capabilities will be added to the product. Refer to our product documentation to see what is already available or planned. For all future feature requirements, we encourage you to open a specific feature request of what you need to integrate into Cockpit.

changelogs.title: New Availability Zone WAW-3
changelogs.description: ADDED: We are excited to introduce our latest Availability Zone (AZ), WAW-3, located in Warsaw, Poland. WAW-3 is now fully operational, providing enhanced accessibility and proximity to support our customers in the Central European region. This comes as the latest development in our commitment to offer an ever-resilient and high-performing cloud infrastructure. Deploy your Instances in WAW-3 now to experience unmatched performance, reliability, and data sovereignty.

changelogs.title: Managed database for Redis now supports the default userna
changelogs.description: CHANGED: You can now use the default username on your managed database for Redis. This enables some software integrations where specific usernames are not supported. Anonymous connection remains unavailable.

changelogs.title: Managed Database now support PostgreSQL 15
changelogs.description: ADDED: This PostgreSQL release brings many improvements. For more information, refer to the PostgreSQL release notes.

changelogs.title: New Cost-optimized and Production-optimized offers
changelogs.description: ADDED: Our Managed Databases offer is complemented with some new Cost-Optimized nodes and the new Production-Optimized range.

news.title: How Kubernetes powers Le Fourgon’s e-commerce & delivery reinvention
news.description: How a French startup reinvented the milkman... with help from Kubernetes!
news.author: James Martin

news.title: How can engineers make IT more sustainable? Part 4: What to do next
news.description: What's next for Green IT? Regulation, and 2050 carbon neutrality targets, will drive a shift from nice-to-have to must-have. And then there's AI...
news.author: James Martin

news.title: Scalers go Open Source: “You don’t know how much you bring to the table.”
news.description: Here’s how Leïla Marabese, one of Scaleway’s Junior DevOps Engineers, got into contributing to open source. In the interview, she shares difficulties, embarrassing mishaps, and, of course, successes.
news.author: Kai Katschthaler

news.title: Zenbleed incident response and vulnerability mitigation
news.description: On 24 July 2023, a vulnerability known as Zenbleed was made public. On that same day, Scaleway patched all of our affected instances to mitigate the vulnerability. Read on for further information.
news.author: Daniel Maher

news.title: The untold story of Elastic Metal
news.description: Until now, managing our offerings was directly done through the service’s database, which created a strong dependency on the Engineering team for updating
news.author: Erwan Paillard

news.title: Help us create the API Gateway that you wish to see in the cloud
news.description: We’re releasing the prototype for a future API Gateway product, and we need your help! Join our early access phase as we develop this exciting new product in the open.
news.author: Simon Shillaker, Jon Regueiro Martin

news.title: Encryption at rest for Instances
news.description: We will guide you through the process of implementing encryption at rest for partitions on a server and how to seamlessly integrate it within an application environment.
news.author: Justin Briard

news.title: How Kubernetes keeps the cloud in perfect harmony - Sacha Bernheim, Padok
news.description: Sacha Bernheim, Lead Site Reliability Engineer at Padok, rolls out K8s solutions for clients on a regular basis. Why is he such a fan of the cloud orchestrator? He explains all here...
news.author: James Martin

news.title: What's new in July? Instances & Elastic Metal power up, K8s insights & more
news.description: Summer is right around the corner. Which isn’t stopping the Scaleway team cranking out new products, events and insights!
news.author: James Martin

news.title: How can engineers make IT more sustainable? Part 3: Green IT case studies
news.description: Green IT can reduce energy consumption by up to 30%... but that's not all! It can also cut server requirements in half, and save huge amounts of CO2 and water. Read on for inspiration!

changelogs.title: Cockpit feature request is completed
changelogs.description: CHANGED: We are happy to announce that we closed one of the most wanted features at Scaleway (open since Jan. 21). Almost every Scaleway products are available in Cockpit for metrics and/or logs. New features and capabilities will be added to the product. Refer to our product documentation to see what is already available or planned. For all future feature requirements, we encourage you to open a specific feature request of what you need to integrate into Cockpit.

changelogs.title: New Availability Zone WAW-3
changelogs.description: ADDED: We are excited to introduce our latest Availability Zone (AZ), WAW-3, located in Warsaw, Poland. WAW-3 is now fully operational, providing enhanced accessibility and proximity to support our customers in the Central European region. This comes as the latest development in our commitment to offer an ever-resilient and high-performing cloud infrastructure. Deploy your Instances in WAW-3 now to experience unmatched performance, reliability, and data sovereignty.

changelogs.title: Managed database for Redis now supports the default userna
changelogs.description: CHANGED: You can now use the default username on your managed database for Redis. This enables some software integrations where specific usernames are not supported. Anonymous connection remains unavailable.

changelogs.title: Managed Database now support PostgreSQL 15
changelogs.description: ADDED: This PostgreSQL release brings many improvements. For more information, refer to the PostgreSQL release notes.

changelogs.title: New Cost-optimized and Production-optimized offers
changelogs.description: ADDED: Our Managed Databases offer is complemented with some new Cost-Optimized nodes and the new Production-Optimized range.

news.title: How Kubernetes powers Le Fourgon’s e-commerce & delivery reinvention
news.description: How a French startup reinvented the milkman... with help from Kubernetes!
news.author: James Martin

news.title: How can engineers make IT more sustainable? Part 4: What to do next
news.description: What's next for Green IT? Regulation, and 2050 carbon neutrality targets, will drive a shift from nice-to-have to must-have. And then there's AI...
news.author: James Martin

news.title: Scalers go Open Source: “You don’t know how much you bring to the table.”
news.description: Here’s how Leïla Marabese, one of Scaleway’s Junior DevOps Engineers, got into contributing to open source. In the interview, she shares difficulties, embarrassing mishaps, and, of course, successes.
news.author: Kai Katschthaler

news.title: Zenbleed incident response and vulnerability mitigation
news.description: On 24 July 2023, a vulnerability known as Zenbleed was made public. On that same day, Scaleway patched all of our affected instances to mitigate the vulnerability. Read on for further information.
news.author: Daniel Maher

news.title: The untold story of Elastic Metal
news.description: Until now, managing our offerings was directly done through the service’s database, which created a strong dependency on the Engineering team for updating
news.author: Erwan Paillard

news.title: Help us create the API Gateway that you wish to see in the cloud
news.description: We’re releasing the prototype for a future API Gateway product, and we need your help! Join our early access phase as we develop this exciting new product in the open.
news.author: Simon Shillaker, Jon Regueiro Martin

news.title: Encryption at rest for Instances
news.description: We will guide you through the process of implementing encryption at rest for partitions on a server and how to seamlessly integrate it within an application environment.
news.author: Justin Briard

news.title: How Kubernetes keeps the cloud in perfect harmony - Sacha Bernheim, Padok
news.description: Sacha Bernheim, Lead Site Reliability Engineer at Padok, rolls out K8s solutions for clients on a regular basis. Why is he such a fan of the cloud orchestrator? He explains all here...
news.author: James Martin

news.title: What's new in July? Instances & Elastic Metal power up, K8s insights & more
news.description: Summer is right around the corner. Which isn’t stopping the Scaleway team cranking out new products, events and insights!
news.author: James Martin

news.title: How can engineers make IT more sustainable? Part 3: Green IT case studies
news.description: Green IT can reduce energy consumption by up to 30%... but that's not all! It can also cut server requirements in half, and save huge amounts of CO2 and water. Read on for inspiration!
news.author: James Martin
